This was the ſtopping of that Bloody Massacre and there was good ground for it; for Lilburn, Osburn, Overton, Prince, and Walwin, perceiving themſelves cheated of their deſign, and that Cromwel called them in onely to keep them quiet, not to yield to any of their demands; and perceiving that Cromwels deſigns were to bring old England into the Spanniſh Mode, that is, to ſet up a Council of State to manage the Affairs of State, and an Inquiſition, or High Court of Iuſtice, to Iudge in matters Criminal; 
                  〈…〉
                into what a Tyrannical road he was got, like open-hearted men did declare to the World, That the way was Tyrannical, and againſt the Liberty of the People, and did proteſt againſt Cromwel as a deceitful Seducer, and a ſubtil Hypocritical Traytor.
